import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['year', 'source']).sum().reset_index()
    
    for source in data_grouped['source'].unique():
        source_data = data_grouped[data_grouped['source'] == source]
        plt.plot(source_data['year'], source_data['net_generation'], label=source)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation (MWh)')
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation of electricity in Iowa from 2001 to 2017?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['net_generation'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Net Generation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation of electricity in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    renewable_data = data[data['source'] == 'Renewables']
    total_net_generation = renewable_data['net_generation'].sum()
    proportions = renewable_data['net_generation'] / total_net_generation
    
    plt.pie(proportions, labels=renewable_data['year'].dt.year, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the proportion of renewable energy sources in the net generation of electricity in Iowa?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
